Chapter: Cite Fn Call

 Probe sample for ONEFOREWORD (docs/Active/Compiler/ONEFOREWORD.md).

 to-unicode is defined in foreword/CCE.codex and is NOT in
 sorted-builtin-names, so unlike is-letter, is-digit, and is-whitespace
 it is not inlined by either compiler builtin dispatch. Its use here
 exercises the real cross-project-function-emission path.

 Observed failure mode before Step 2: codex build succeeds silently and
 emits samples/cite-fn-call.cs, but the generated C sharp calls
 to_unicode(13L) with no definition; dotnet build on the output fails
 with CS0103.

 When Step 2 of ONEFOREWORD lands (cross-project function emission in
 codex-cli), this sample compiles and prints 101 on both paths.

  cites Foreword chapter CCE

Section: Definitions

  main : [Console] Nothing = act
    print-line ("to-unicode 13 = " ++ show (to-unicode 13))
  end

